---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Is FE a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)" description="FE is a valid Scrabble word worth 5 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. A Hebrew letter (variant of pe). One of the highest-scoring 2-letter words in Scrabble." keywords="is fe a scrabble word, fe scrabble, fe valid scrabble, fe points scrabble, two letter f words, fe meaning scrabble, high scoring two letter words">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Is FE a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)","description":"FE is a valid Scrabble word worth 5 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. A Hebrew letter (variant of pe).","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-fe-a-scrabble-word"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is FE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, FE is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 5 points (F=4, E=1) and is a variant spelling of the Hebrew letter pe (the 17th letter of the Hebrew alphabet)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is FE a high-scoring 2-letter word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"FE scores 5 points because F is worth 4 points — one of the higher-value consonants. This makes FE tied with HE, HO, IF, OF as a 5-point 2-letter word. It's ideal for scoring when board space is tight."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What words can extend FE?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"FE extends into FED (7pts), FEE (6pts), FEN (6pts), FER (6pts), FES (6pts), FET (6pts), FEW (9pts), FEY (9pts), FEZ (15pts). FEZ is particularly valuable at 15 points with Z(10)."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is FE a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, FE is a valid Scrabble word worth 5 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's a variant spelling of the Hebrew letter pe (the 17th letter of the Hebrew alphabet). At 5 points, FE is one of the highest-scoring 2-letter words — F alone contributes 4 points, making it a premium short play.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">FE</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">5 points · F=4, E=1 · A Hebrew letter (variant of pe)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). FE is a high-value 2-letter word thanks to F being worth 4 points. One of the best short plays for tight board positions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2 F-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Top 10</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">2-Letter Score</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">FE Extensions: High-Value Builds</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEZ</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEW</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEY</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FED</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why FE Is a Power Play</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">5 points for 2 tiles:</span> Most 2-letter words score 2-4 points. FE at 5 is premium territory, matching words like HE, IF, and OF. On a DWS, that's 10 points from just 2 tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for FEZ:</span> FEZ scores 15 points — one of the highest 3-letter words. Play FE near a Z-accessible square and extend next turn for massive returns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">F on premium squares:</span> With F worth 4 points, landing it on a DLS gives you 8 from one tile. FE on a DLS+DWS combination scores 18 points — exceptional for a 2-letter play.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Scoring Comparison</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Among 2-letter words, FE ranks in the <span class="text-white font-medium">top tier at 5 points</span>. Only ZA (11pts), XI (9pts), XU (9pts), JO (9pts), QI (11pts), and a few others score higher. FE is the best F-word short play available.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-if-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is IF a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-em-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is EM a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
